  "author_association": "NONE",
  "body": "I've ran into the following issue: I deployed rook on a 2-worker-node setup, and it worked fine. Then, I removed the node with IP `10.10.116.115` and added a new one. Since the new worker node has a different IP address, the `Node-Selectors` bit does not match anymore, thus scheduling the `mon` pod is impossible and fails.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure where to start debugging this, or what solution would be possible to this problem. We constantly replace our worker nodes, as they are immutable and get created from scratch with new IPs every time.\r\n\r\n```\r\nNode-Selectors:\tkubernetes.io/hostname=10.10.116.115\r\nTolerations:\t<none>\r\nEvents:\r\n  FirstSeen\tLastSeen\tCount\tFrom\t\t\tSubObjectPath\tType\t\tReason\t\t\tMessage\r\n  ---------\t--------\t-----\t----\t\t\t-------------\t--------\t------\t\t\t-------\r\n  7m\t\t3s\t\t29\tdefault-scheduler\t\t\tWarning\t\tFailedScheduling\tNo nodes are available that match all of the following predicates:: MatchNodeSelector (1).\r\n```",
  "closed_at": "2017-11-15T00:14:00Z",
